  "prompt": "What colours complement amber?",
  "response": "Amber is a warm, golden-orange hue. Complementary colors for amber can include both cool and warm tones that create a balanced and aesthetically pleasing combination. Some colors that complement amber are:\n\n1. **Teal**: This blue-green color offers a striking contrast to amber's warm tones.\n2. **Navy Blue**: A deep, rich blue can enhance the warmth of amber.\n3. **Burgundy**: A dark, reddish-purple color brings out the richness of amber.\n4. **Olive Green**: A muted, earthy green complements amber well.\n5. **Charcoal Gray**: This neutral color balances amber's brightness.\n6. **Soft Pastel Peach**: A lighter, muted version of amber can harmonize beautifully.\n7. **Cream or Ivory**: These soft, neutral colors provide a subtle contrast.\n8. **Turquoise**: This vibrant blue-green color contrasts nicely with golden amber.\n9. **Plum**: A rich, dark purple adds depth and contrast to amber.\n\nCombining these colors with amber in design or decor can create visually appealing and harmonious results.",
